data.content:
**Yes, C# fully supports `stackalloc`'d `Span<nint>` and `Span<nuint>`.** Both compiled and ran without issues on .NET 10:

```csharp
Span<nint>  signedSpan   = stackalloc nint[5];
Span<nuint> unsignedSpan = stackalloc nuint[5];
```

This has been supported since C# 9 / .NET 5 when `nint`/`nuint` were introduced as first-class types (aliases for `System.IntPtr`/`System.UIntPtr`). They work with `stackalloc` just like `int`, `long`, or any other unmanaged type.
